              "data_type": "str, optional",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "This parameter specifies the method to use for estimating the\npercentile.  There are many different methods, some unique to NumPy.\nSee the notes for explanation.  The options sorted by their R type\nas summarized in the H&F paper "
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "[1]_"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": " are:"
                }
              ],
              "name": "method",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "If this is set to True, the axes which are reduced are left in\nthe result as dimensions with size one. With this option, the\nresult will broadcast correctly against the original array "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "If this is anything but the default value it will be passed\nthrough (in the special case of an empty array) to the\n"
                    },
                    {
                      "external_url": "",
                      "href": "/docs/api/ops/mean",
                      "kind": "link",
                      "target": "mean",
                      "text": "mean"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " function of the underlying array.  If the array is\na sub-class and "
                    },
                    {
                      "external_url": "",
                      "href": "/docs/api/ops/mean",
                      "kind": "link",
                      "target": "mean",
                      "text": "mean"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " does not have the kwarg "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "keepdims"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " this\nwill raise a RuntimeError."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "bool, optional",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "If this is set to True, the axes which are reduced are left in\nthe result as dimensions with size one. With this option, the\nresult will broadcast correctly against the original array "
                },
                {
                  "kind": "code",
                  "text": "a"
                },
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ],
              "name": "keepdims",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "An array of weights associated with the values in "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ". Each value in\n"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " contributes to the percentile according to its associated weight.\nThe weights array can either be 1-D (in which case its length must be\nthe size of "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " along the given axis) or of the same shape as "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ".\nIf "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "weights=None"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ", then all data in "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " are assumed to have a\nweight equal to one.\nOnly "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "method=\"inverted_cdf\""
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " supports weights."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
